President Trump delivered a speech at the U.S. Air Force Academy graduation ceremony, praising the Class of 2019 and highlighting their achievements. He thanked Secretary Heather Wilson and other notable figures in attendance. The President emphasized the importance of the Air Force in protecting and defending the United States and praised the graduates for their commitment to service. He also discussed the investments made in the military, including the development of new technologies and the establishment of the Space Force. President Trump concluded by congratulating the graduates and expressing his confidence in their ability to uphold America's legacy of leadership in the world.